(54, 2, '2010-09-21 12:28:37', '2010-09-21 12:28:37', 'Withens Clough Reservoir is like a forgotten land- down on the edge of the water, the stumps of old drowned trees that I assume are usually under the waterline but for the lack of rainfall.\n\n<a rel="attachment wp-att-52" href="http://watershed.sallybarker.local/withens-clough-reservoir/withens-clough-beach/"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-52" title="Withens Clough beach" src="http://watershed.sallybarker.local/files/2010/09/Withens-Clough-beach-640x426.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="426" /></a>\n\nthe mud is gorgeous - black , smooth, a bit claggy so good to model with. Its like a cross between clay &amp; peat.So I dug some up with a stone, to make sculpture back at home - out of the relentless heavy drizzle and whipping rain- Frankie, my lurcher, offered advice-<a href="../wp-content/uploads/2010/09/digging-at-withens-clough.jpg?phpMyAdmin=e34384b0610b57fdc53943617a6f8057"><img title="digging at withens clough" src="../wp-content/uploads/2010/09/digging-at-withens-clough-300x200.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="200" /></a>', 'Withens Clough Reservoir', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '29-autosave', '', '', '2010-09-21 12:28:37', '2010-09-21 12:28:37', '', 29, 'http://watershed.sallybarker.local/29-autosave/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
