(367, 2, '2011-03-20 15:32:11', '2011-03-20 15:32:11', '<a rel="attachment wp-att-366" href="http://watershed.sallybarker.local/?attachment_id=366"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-366" src="http://watershed.sallybarker.local/files/2011/03/3-trig-point1-640x413.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="413" /></a>these trig points act as focal  punctuation marks - they dot the landscape: stark, white, concrete and minimal. Superceded now by GPS and aerial mapping but still used a lot by hikers. The metal bracket on the top would have held a theodolite. I love the way their obelisk shape looks so incongruous in the middle of nowhere. Hence the people, standing around, as if waiting for something of some significance to occur.\n\n&nbsp;', 'trig point- High Brown Knoll', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '364-revision', '', '', '2011-03-20 15:32:11', '2011-03-20 15:32:11', '', 364, 'http://watershed.sallybarker.local/364-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
