(277, 3, '2012-01-18 17:07:25', '2012-01-18 16:07:25', '&nbsp;\n\n<span style="font-family: Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">experimental, fun and thought provoking in a physical way</span></span>\n\n<span style="font-family: Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">This day long workshop was held with 8 adults, with no specific physical requirements . Body drawing workshops are tailored to fit the needs &amp; number of participants and the size and physical detail of the venue. Any age, ability and level of fitness. </span></span>\n\n<span style="font-family: Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">The floor and up the walls are papered, potentially furniture too. The group physically explore the 3D space and are led through relaxation &amp; breathing excercises, body awareness, trust building, exploratory individual mark making,intimate and private drawing, choreographed group work, finally turning the whole 2D drawing into a sculptural installation, getting inside &amp; drawing with torches. The paper can be torn up to take home!</span></span>\n\n<span style="font-family: Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">The emphasis is on experimental, thoughtful mark making and drawing with lots of opportunity to share thoughts, self and peer critique/ direction and laughing!</span></span>\n\n<span style="font-family: Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">Mess &amp; dirty clothes is essential.</span></span>\n\n<span style="font-family: Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">For images of different drawing groups please go to <strong>the drawing shed</strong> </span></span>', 'group drawing days- case study', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '267-revision', '', '', '2012-01-18 17:07:25', '2012-01-18 16:07:25', '', 267, 'http://sallybarker.local/uncategorized/267-revision/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(278, 3, '2012-01-19 13:33:56', '2012-01-19 12:33:56', '<span style="font-family: Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: small;">I like to use strange and forgotten or overlooked spaces that, when given some attention and nurturing with the childrens work, results in something very positive, powerful and meaningful. They can represent the un-beautiful, the imperfect but interesting and characterful. When we give attention to something previuosly missed we celebrate the act of looking closer at our environment. These displays in neglected spaces invests in ourselves,and  create a form of community.</span></span>\n\nI have a lot of experience exhibiting my own and a wide range of other peoples work in a', 'display in neglected spaces', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '114-revision-2', '', '', '2012-01-19 13:33:56', '2012-01-19 12:33:56', '', 114, 'http://sallybarker.local/uncategorized/114-revision-2/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(279, 3, '2012-01-19 13:35:57', '2012-01-19 12:35:57', '<span style="font-family: Arial,sans-serif;">Example of a workshop for the extended schools programme in Calderdale, mod-roc sculpture, family drop-in workshop, with 200 people over 3 hour session. Making a variety of mod-roc sculpture, mostly from a selection of model animals.</span>\n\n<span style="font-family: Arial,sans-serif;">I have lost count of the number of workshops I''ve run with mod-roc. It''s a wonderful , malleable, and beautiful material that is very easy to use but also great for extending skills- you can achieve very intricate, controlled modelling work but it also has great sensory potential as it has to be smoothed to work properly- good for taking moulds from body parts.</span>\n\n<span style="font-family: Arial,sans-serif;">Good for making trees. I have a collection of mod-roc trees for sale from £20.</span>\n\n&nbsp;', 'mod-roc workshop ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '68-revision-2', '', '', '2012-01-19 13:35:57', '2012-01-19 12:35:57', '', 68, 'http://sallybarker.local/uncategorized/68-revision-2/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
