(302, 3, '2012-01-19 16:07:28', '2012-01-19 15:07:28', '<span style="font-family: Arial,sans-serif;">For five years I worked for a small organisation called TAS- therapeutic arts organistion, in Waltham Forest, London.</span>\n\n<span style="font-family: Arial,sans-serif;">We worked with referred, at risk and excluded children in small groups. Projects were creatively led by me and a small team of experienced professionals. Most of this work was supported by creative therapists (art, dance and music) whom I worked very collaboratively with. The projects were many and varied: short holiday projects lasting a few days; an after school project lasting 2 years ;a group of boys in a PRU etc. </span>\n\n<span style="font-family: Arial,sans-serif;">This was always sensitive work with often very vulnerable, hard to reach children, who I feel extremely priviledged to have worked with. </span>\n\n<span style="font-family: Arial,sans-serif;">Our aims were to raise self esteem , by offering the children an open creative space to express themselves, develop their emotional health, cope with their own behaviour and ultimately be happier. </span>', 'TAS - creatively led,therapeutically supported', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '159-revision-2', '', '', '2012-01-19 16:07:28', '2012-01-19 15:07:28', '', 159, 'http://sallybarker.local/uncategorized/159-revision-2/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
