(549, 3, '2012-12-01 23:28:43', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'I was the first year artist on the three year project called “<span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: medium;">The Watershed- Inspired by  Landscape” - a Heritage Lottery funded commission to make a new body of work in response to the moorland landscape of the south pennines and to develop a new visiting audience.(WLP is currently a finalist in the National Lottery Awards for best environmental project) My work continued previuos themes exploring our relationship with the landscape, our mark and our success, researching its geography, geology, socio- historical presence. I scavenged materials to make sculptural responses, which I photographed back in the landscape.</span></span>\n\n<span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: medium;"> I exhibited these large images and a sculptural installation at Cartwright Hall Art Gallery. I took several groups of people up onto the moors to make work in situ, many, like a group of students with disabilities, had never been in this landscape before. Collaborating with the Watershed poet Andrew McMillan making geo-caches installed in the landscape, to encourage journeys, new ways of looking, experiencing and relating the landscape to our lives. I enjoyed working with someone using a different artform - exploring common themes and strands of thought and how the work might be delivered and accessed by a wider audience. We ran many workshops with different groups and held a talk on my work.</span></span>', 'The Watershed - Inspired by Landscape Project', '', 'draft', 'closed', 'closed', '', '', '', '', '2012-12-01 23:28:43', '2012-12-01 22:28:43', '', 0, 'http://sallybarker.local/?post_type=art&#038;p=549', 2, 'art', '', 0),
