(572, 3, '2012-09-24 17:31:57', '2012-09-24 16:31:57', '"Scaffolding with Nepenthes" sets up a drama, as we anticipate the contact between the spiky scaffolding and the soft skin of the nepenthes plant.\r\n\r\nThe complex structure made with glued together grass from the moors, has the appearance of model scale scaffolding, occupied by the painted figures. The Nepenthes has pendulous, fleshy pitchers  containing water- which seem to embody both male and female sexual parts simultaneously. In the tropics the fleshy looking pitchers attract insects to its rim, they slide down into the pool of water which contains secretions to digest the nutrients from the insect. Nepenthese in Greek , means without grief.\r\n\r\nHere is a  combination of glorious and attractive carniverous plant  with a hand-made spiky structure that in itself, points aggressively towards the plants soft, phallus like skin. It was shown in Temporary Artspace exhibition in Wakefield.', 'Scaffolding with Nepenthese', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'scaffolding-with-nepenthese', '', '', '2012-12-01 23:28:44', '2012-12-01 22:28:44', '', 0, 'http://sallybarker.local/?post_type=art&#038;p=572', 7, 'art', '', 0),
(573, 3, '2012-10-02 23:48:10', '2012-10-02 22:48:10', 'I will be resident artist at Foxhill Bank Park , Oswaldtwistle, from October 14th to November 4th 2012 as part of a Curious Minds project connecting 6 artists to 6 parks in E. Lancashire. I will be doing creatively led research on site , and in a studio, to  investigate how the park is used and explore the relationship between local people and their environment.', 'Foxhill Bank Park and Nature Reserve', 'I will be resident artist at Foxhill Bank Park , Oswaldtwistle, from October 14th to November 4th 2012 ', 'draft', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'foxhill', '', '', '2012-12-01 23:33:18', '2012-12-01 22:33:18', '', 0, 'http://sallybarker.local/?post_type=art&#038;p=573', 4, 'art', '', 0),
